-- China Plans Five-Day Military Exercise in Central Provinces, Xinhua Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-08-03T00:01:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-03/china-plans-five-day-military-exercise-in-central-provinces-xinhua-says.html

          
          
             China is planning to hold a five-day
military exercise in the provinces of Henan and Shandong from
today, the official Xinhua News Agency reported.  
 The drills, code-named “Vanguard-2010,” will involve
12,000 soldiers and officers from China’s air defense force,
Xinhua reported late yesterday, citing an unidentified person at
the People’s Liberation Army’s Jinan Military Command. An
undisclosed number of reconnaissance planes, combat aircraft and
helicopters will also take part in the exercise, Xinhua
reported.  
          
          


  


        